### Recruiter API Batch Upload & WebSocket Tests
### REST Client for testing recruiter endpoints

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8001/api/v1/recruiter
@authToken = Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
@orgId = 1
@jobId = 1
@taskId = placeholder_task_id

###
### SETUP: Get Auth Token (if needed)
POST http://localhost:8001/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "recruiter@example.com",
  "password": "password"
}

###
### TEST 1: List Jobs (Pagination)
GET @baseUrl/jobs?limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 2: Get Candidates with Pagination
GET @baseUrl/candidates?limit=20&offset=0
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 3: Test Pagination Limit Validation (should pass for 1-1000)
GET @baseUrl/candidates?limit=500&offset=0
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 4: Test Pagination Limit Validation (should fail for >1000)
GET @baseUrl/candidates?limit=1500&offset=0
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 5: Search with Pagination
GET @baseUrl/search?query=python&limit=50&offset=0&job_id=1
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 6: Export Candidates as CSV
GET @baseUrl/export/candidates?format=csv
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 7: Export Candidates as JSON
GET @baseUrl/export/candidates?format=json
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 8: Export Rankings as CSV
GET @baseUrl/export/rankings?format=csv&job_id=1
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 9: Export Rankings as JSON
GET @baseUrl/export/rankings?format=json&job_id=1
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

###
### TEST 10: Bulk Email Endpoint (Email Validation)
POST @baseUrl/send-email-bulk
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Job Opportunity",
  "body": "We have an exciting opportunity for you",
  "recipients": [
    {
      "candidate_id": 1,
      "email": "candidate1@example.com"
    },
    {
      "candidate_id": 2,
      "email": "invalid-email"
    }
  ]
}

###
### TEST 11: Bulk Email - Max Recipients (100 limit)
POST @baseUrl/send-email-bulk
Authorization: @authToken
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Bulk Test",
  "body": "Testing bulk email with 101 recipients",
  "recipients": [
    {
      "candidate_id": 1,
      "email": "candidate1@example.com"
    }
  ]
}

###
### TEST 12: Batch Upload CVs (Must be multipart form-data)
### NOTE: This requires actual PDF files. Run via curl:
### 
### AUTH_HEADER="$(printf 'Authorization:%sBearer %s' ' ' "$JWT_TOKEN")"
### curl -X POST \
###   -H "$AUTH_HEADER" \
###   -F "job_id=1" \
###   -F "files=@/path/to/cv1.pdf" \
###   -F "files=@/path/to/cv2.pdf" \
###   http://localhost:8001/api/v1/recruiter/dashboard/batch-upload

POST @baseUrl/dashboard/batch-upload
Authorization: @authToken

{
  "job_id": 1,
  "files": "Binary PDF files here"
}

###
### TEST 13: WebSocket Batch Upload Progress
### NOTE: This requires WebSocket client. 
### 
### Via JavaScript:
### 
### const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8001/api/v1/recruiter/ws/batch-upload/YOUR_TASK_ID');
### ws.onmessage = (event) => {
###   const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
###   console.log('Progress:', data);
###   // Expected: { status, processed, total, percent, current_file, error? }
### };

GRAPHQL ws://localhost:8001/api/v1/recruiter/ws/batch-upload/@taskId

###
### TEST 14: Rate Limiting Check (60 requests/minute)
GET @baseUrl/candidates
Authorization: @authToken

# Make multiple requests quickly to trigger 429 Too Many Requests

###
### TEST 15: Permission Check (Cross-org isolation)
GET @baseUrl/candidates
Authorization: @differentOrgAuthToken

# Should not return candidates from different organization

###
### NOTES:
### - All GET endpoints support pagination: ?limit=1-1000&offset=0+
### - Rate limiting: 60 requests/minute per endpoint
### - Batch upload: Max 50 files, 5MB per file, PDF/TXT/DOCX only
### - WebSocket: Auto-closes when status = SUCCESS or FAILURE
### - All timestamps in UTC ISO 8601 format
### - Error responses include 'detail' field with error message

